# ADAS Compact Model — Jetson Nano 4GB

Real-time 5-task ADAS system running at ~25 FPS on Jetson Nano 4GB.
One single model handles everything in one forward pass.

---

## Tasks
| Task | Model Head | Dataset |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Object detection | Detection head | BDD100K |
| Lane detection | Lane head | CULane |
| Drivable area | Segmentation head | BDD100K + Cityscapes |
| Traffic signs | Sign head | Mapillary Signs |
| Traffic lights | Light head | BOSCH Lights |

---

## Architecture
- Backbone : EfficientNet-B2 (shared by all tasks)
- Neck     : BiFPN (multi-scale feature fusion)
- Heads    : 5 task-specific heads
- Runtime  : TensorRT INT8 on Jetson Nano

---

## Performance on Jetson Nano
| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| FPS | ~25 |
| Latency | ~38ms |
| GPU memory | ~2.2 GB |
| Model size | ~50 MB (.trt) |

---

## How to use

### 1 — Train (PC or Google Colab)
pip install -r requirements.txt
python data/convert.py
python training/train.py

### 2 — Export
python export/export_onnx.py
bash export/build_trt.sh        # run this ON the Nano

### 3 — Run on Jetson Nano
bash deploy/setup_nano.sh
python deploy/inference.py --source /dev/video0

---

## Project structure
data/       — dataset download and conversion
models/     — backbone, neck, heads, losses
training/   — training loop and config
export/     — ONNX and TensorRT conversion
deploy/     — Jetson Nano inference pipeline
